                    Here is a list of fun facts about Pocky:
                </h3>
                <p>
                <ul id="fun-facts">
                    <li>Pocky was launched in 1966, and at the time each stick was hand dipped in chocolate.</li><br />
                    <li>The name "Pocky" was inspired by the sound made when eating the snack.</li><br />
                    <li>In Malaysia, Pocky used to be called "Rocky" for over 40 years.</li><br />
                    <li>Pocky is known as "Mikado" in many European countries.</li><br />
                    <li>Pocky is sold in over 50 flavors total, including: chocolate, strawberry, almond, banana,
                        caramel,
                        melon, and many more!</li><br />
                    <li>"My Calorie Pocky" is a lighter version of the snack which contains one-fourth the calories of
                        regular Pocky.</li><br />
                    <li>A savory snack which is related to Pocky is "Pretz," which is an unglazed biscuit featuring
                        flavors such as tomato and salad.</li><br />
                    <li>November 11th is known as "Pocky & Pretz Day" in Japan. (The repeated number 1 in the numerical
                        date represents the shape of Pocky.)</li><br />
                </ul>
                </p>
